# Deploying the policy tracker + council voting records to GitHub

Both tools live in ONE repo: `upp-vuaa.github.io` (the same repo serving the
meetings tracker). The daily workflow runs both scripts and publishes into
`policy/`, so the pages land at:

- Dashboard: https://upp-vuaa.github.io/policy/
- Council records: https://upp-vuaa.github.io/policy/council.html

## Web UI (no tools needed)

1. Unzip `policy-tracker.zip` locally → you get a `policy-tracker/` folder.
2. On github.com, open the `upp-vuaa.github.io` repo → **Add file → Upload
   files** → drag the whole `policy-tracker` folder in → commit to `main`.
   (The hidden `.github` subfolder inside it usually won't upload — fine,
   next step handles the workflow.)
3. Create the workflow at the repo ROOT: **Add file → Create new file** →
   name it exactly `.github/workflows/track.yml` (typing the slashes creates
   the folders) → paste the contents of `policy-tracker/.github/workflows/track.yml`
   → commit. **This location matters:** Actions only runs workflows from the
   root `.github/workflows/`, never from inside a subfolder.
4. **Settings → Actions → General → Workflow permissions** → select
   **Read and write permissions** → Save. (The bot commits nightly data
   files; without this the push fails with a 403.)
5. **Actions tab → policy-tracker → Run workflow → main.** First run takes
   ~2–4 min — the zip ships the backfilled vote ledger, so council.py runs
   incrementally instead of redoing 24 months.
6. Open the two URLs above. Give Pages a minute or two after the commit.

## Command line (equivalent)

    git clone https://github.com/upp-vuaa/upp-vuaa.github.io
    cd upp-vuaa.github.io
    cp -r /path/to/policy-tracker .
    mkdir -p .github/workflows
    cp policy-tracker/.github/workflows/track.yml .github/workflows/
    git add . && git commit -m "Add policy tracker + council records" && git push

Then do steps 4–6 above.

## Ongoing

- Runs daily at 6:00 AM Phoenix (13:00 UTC); trigger manually anytime from
  the Actions tab.
- Edit `policy-tracker/members.json`, `positions.json`, or `vote_weights.json`
  right in the GitHub web UI (pencil icon); changes apply on the next run.
  members.json is never overwritten by the scraper.
- First dashboard run establishes the "What moved" baseline — expected.
- No secrets or tokens needed; everything is public data + the built-in
  GITHUB_TOKEN.

## If something misbehaves

- Action fails on the push step → step 4 (workflow permissions) wasn't set.
- Pages look stale → hard-refresh; confirm Settings → Pages source is
  "Deploy from a branch: main / (root)" (already true if the meetings
  tracker is live).
- Broadened topic keywords later → clear `council_state.json` to re-scrape;
  tightening keywords needs nothing (re-tag is automatic).
